Explanation:

Apply Malus's Law twice. Initial unpolarized light halves ($-> I/2$). Through the next $45^degree$ filter: $(I/2)cos^2(45^degree) = I/4$. Through the final horizontal filter ($45^degree$ further): $(I/4)cos^2(45^degree) = I/8$.
